        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(config): accept transport: \"stdio\" in MCP server validation (fixes #95082)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAccept explicit `transport: \"stdio\"` for command-bearing MCP server definitions.\n\n`openclaw config validate` previously rejected this redundant transport spelling even though the runtime already selects stdio whenever a valid `command` is present. The schema and exported config type now match that existing runtime contract.\n\nFixes #95082.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Add `stdio` to the MCP server transport schema.\n- Align the exported `McpServerConfig.transport` union and its documentation.\n- Add focused regression coverage for accepted `stdio` and rejected unsupported transport values.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/config/schema.test.ts src/config/mcp-config.test.ts src/agents/mcp-transport-config.test.ts` (66 tests passed)\n- `git diff --check`\n- Fresh Codex autoreview: no accepted/actionable findings, correctness confidence 0.98.\n- Direct Codex contract check: `../codex/codex-rs/config/src/mcp_types.rs` selects stdio from `command` and has no OpenClaw transport discriminator.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Explicit `transport: \"stdio\"` is accepted for command-bearing MCP servers, matching the existing runtime path.\n\nReal environment tested: Isolated OpenClaw state directory on macOS with the repository CLI.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `openclaw mcp set demo '{\"command\":\"node\",\"args\":[\"server.mjs\"],\"transport\":\"stdio\"}'`, followed by `openclaw config validate`.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\n$ OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=/tmp/openclaw-pr-95083-fixed node scripts/run-node.mjs mcp set demo '{\"command\":\"node\",\"args\":[\"server.mjs\"],\"transport\":\"stdio\"}'\nSaved MCP server \"demo\" to /tmp/openclaw-pr-95083-fixed/openclaw.json.\n\n$ OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR=/tmp/openclaw-pr-95083-fixed node scripts/run-node.mjs config validate\nConfig valid: /tmp/openclaw-pr-95083-fixed/openclaw.json\n```\n\nBaseline evidence:\n\n```text\nConfig invalid after MCP set (mcp.servers.demo.transport: Invalid input (allowed: \"sse\", \"streamable-http\")).\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: Schema validation, exported TypeScript configuration, runtime transport resolution, and the Codex projection agree on command-based stdio behavior.\n\nWhat was not tested: No external MCP child process was launched; this PR does not change process launch behavior.\n",
        "branch": "fix/config-validate-mcp-stdio-transport",
